modules.description: Parses structured data from byte streams using monadic and applicative combinators, supporting backtracking and lookahead for flexible input handling. Works with byte buffers and input sources, enabling efficient processing of network protocols and serialized formats. Used to implement protocol parsers like HTTP and JSON, with control over memory and I/O behavior.

Provides functions to parse input from a channel using a parser, supporting both single and repeated parsing operations. Works with `Angstrom.t` parsers and `Lwt_io.input_channel` to process data incrementally. Enables resuming parsing from a saved state using `Buffered.state`, useful for handling large or streaming data sources.
